Police arrested three alleged hijackers yesterday near the Grayston off-ramp following a shootout. JOHANNESBURG - Police say theyre interrogating three suspects arrestedin a shootout with officers on the M1 highway to try and trace the fourth suspect. The alleged hijackers were arrested yesterday near the Grayston off-ramp; one of them was wounded. Police say the menare also linked to a string ofrobberies in KwaZulu-Natal. The polices Kay Makhubele says they will now face additionalcharges,includingrobbery,attempted murder andhijacking. Interrogating the other suspects is part of our investigation and at the moment we havent got a lead of his whereabouts but a manhunt is underway for him. WATCH: Cops arrest 3 in Sandton shootout